  {
    "id": "task-stall-detect-001",
    "title": "Fix stall detection \u2014 316-min task was not caught",
    "assignee": "monkey",
    "status": "done",
    "priority": "P1",
    "ts": "2026-06-04T11:56:14.368287+00:00",
    "note": "The browser automation task (task-browser-auto-001) was in_progress for 316+ minutes without being caught by stall detection. Root cause: stall detection only fires on heartbeat, and the task had no lastActivity timestamp updates. The task was created with ts='just now' and never updated.\n\nFix:\n1. Review stall detection logic in HEARTBEAT.md \u2014 is the threshold correct?\n2. Check if tasks with ts='just now' (non-parseable) are being handled correctly\n3. Add a safety net: if a task has been in_progress for >60 min with no lastActivity, flag it regardless of heartbeat timing\n4. Consider adding a max time limit per dispatch (e.g., 30 min auto-reset if no progress)\n5. Test the fix by creating a test task and verifying stall detection catches it",
    "tags": [
      "bug",
      "stall-detection",
      "heartbeat",
      "reliability"
    ],
    "history": [
      {
        "ts": "2026-06-04T11:56:14.368287+00:00",
        "action": "created",
        "actor": "monkey",
        "details": "Created from Kanban sense check \u2014 stall detection gap identified"
      },
      {
        "ts": "2026-06-04T12:09:32.904287+00:00",
        "action": "completed",
        "actor": "monkey",
        "details": "Stall detection fix complete \u2014 3-min investigation, logic updated in HEARTBEAT.md"
      }
    ],
    "lastActivity": "2026-06-04T12:09:32.904287+00:00",
    "currentStep": "Completed",
    "progress": 100,
    "completedAt": "2026-06-04T12:09:32.904287+00:00",
    "summary": "Fixed stall detection gap that let browser-auto task sit in_progress for 316+ minutes.\n\nRoot cause: task created with ts=\"just now\" (non-parseable) and no lastActivity. Sub-agent never updated lastActivity (ghost dispatch). Stall detection skipped ts=\"just now\" and had no fallback until 2-hour threshold.\n\nChanges to HEARTBEAT.md:\n1. HARD RULE: any in_progress task with no lastActivity for >30 min = immediate reset\n2. history[].ts (including created event) now used as fallback timestamp\n3. Task creation now always sets lastActivity to current ISO timestamp\n4. Task Pickup requires lastActivity set BEFORE dispatch\n5. Browser auto-task ts fixed to parseable ISO from history\n\nNo task can now sit in_progress for >30 min without being caught by stall detection."
  },
