d (older entries)\n- Memory page (older daily logs)\n\n\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\n4. MAKE INCIDENTS PAGE FILTERS CLICKABLE\n\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\n\nThe Incidents page shows \"46 tracked \u00b7 6 open \u00b7 3 critical\" but \nthese aren't clickable \u2014 they don't filter the list. The Tasks page \nhas working filters (All, Operational, Features) that filter the \nKanban when clicked.\n\nMake the Incidents page filters work the same way:\n- Click \"6 open\" \u2192 shows only open incidents\n- Click \"3 critical\" \u2192 shows only critical/P1 incidents\n- Click \"46 tracked\" \u2192 shows all\n- Active filter should be highlighted (same style as Tasks page filters)\n- The count badges should update as filters change\n\nThis makes the Incidents page consistent with the Tasks page UX.\n\n\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\n5. ADD TO FRAMEWORK.MD\n\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\n\nAdd these gotchas:\n- \"setAwaitingReviewCount crash: SSR fails if a state setter is passed \n  as a prop but never defined. The page renders blank.\"\n- \"node:path static imports: replaced with lazy await import() inside \n  server function handlers. Never statically import Node.js built-ins \n  in files that could be imported by client components.\"\n- \"P1 Dashboard blank page: first check the SSR error in the HTML source \n  (view-source) before chasing client bun