    "ts": "just now",
    "note": "Task Completion \u2014 summary and visibility improvement.\n\nThe auto-move from In Progress to Done works well. But when a task \nmoves to Done, I can't tell WHAT was actually done. The card just \nsays \"Done\" with no context.\n\nFix:\n\n1. When a task completes and auto-moves to Done, the card must \n   include a brief summary of what was accomplished. This summary \n   should be:\n   - Written by the agent that completed the task\n   - 1-3 sentences describing the actual outcome\n   - Stored on the task card itself, visible in the Kanban view\n   - Also visible when I click \"More Details\" on the card\n\n2. The \"More Details\" view on any Done card should show:\n   - Original task description\n   - Completion summary (what was actually done)\n   - Which agent completed it\n   - Timestamp of completion\n   - Any relevant links or artifacts produced (files changed, \n     commits made, etc.)\n\n3. In the Kanban view, a Done card should show at minimum:\n   - Task title\n   - One-line completion summary (truncated if needed)\n   - \"Done by [Agent] \u2022 [time]\"\n\n4. If the task was created manually by me (not auto-generated from \n   an error or cron job), the agent who picks it up should write \n   the completion summary before moving it to Done. If no summary \n   is written, the task should NOT auto-move \u2014 it should stay In \n   Progress with a flag: \"Awaiting completion summary.\"\n\nThis applies to ALL tasks going forward. Retroactively fixing old \nDone tasks is optional \u2014 only if quick.\n\nReport your approach before implementing.",
