  {
    "id": "task-mp7cbyxz-0ztq",
    "title": "Error Feed \u2014 behaviour review and fix.",
    "assignee": "lifesupport",
    "status": "done",
    "priority": "P3",
    "ts": "just now",
    "note": "Error Feed \u2014 behaviour review and fix.\n\nThe error feed currently has Investigate / Resolved / Skip buttons but \nthe workflow is confusing. Here's how it should actually work:\n\n\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\nCORRECT ERROR FEED WORKFLOW\n\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\n\n1. A cron job fails \u2192 error appears in the Error Feed tab with a \n   \"NEW\" badge\n\n2. I click \"Investigate\" \u2192 \n   - The error status changes to \"IN PROGRESS\" \n   - A corresponding task is automatically created in the Tasks \n     section under \"In Progress\" so the crew knows to work on it\n   - The error stays visible in the feed with an in-progress indicator\n   - The button changes to show \"Resolved\" and \"Skip\"\n\n3. The crew fixes the underlying issue. The cron job runs successfully \n   on its next scheduled run \u2192\n   - The error automatically clears from the Error Feed\n   - The linked task in the Tasks section moves to \"Done\"\n   - No manual \"Resolved\" click needed \u2014 the system verified the fix\n\n4. If I click \"Resolved\" manually \u2192\n   - For when I've verified the fix myself\n   - Error disappears from the feed\n   - Linked task moves to Done\n\n5. If I click \"Skip\" \u2192\n   - For known non-critical issues I'm choosing to ignore\n   - Error disappears from the feed\n   - No task is created\n\n6. If the same job fails again later \u2192\n   - A NEW error appears (not the old one reopened)\n   - Fresh timestamp, fresh status\n   - Does NOT resurrect the old skipped/resolved error\n\n\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\nKEY RULES\n\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\n\n- Errors should NOT show \"Completed\" with an \"In Progress\" flag \n  at the same time (current bug)\n- When a cron job succeeds after being in error state, the error \n  should auto-clear \u2014 the system verified the fix\n- The \"Investigate\" button creates a task in the Tasks board so \n  work is tracked\n- The error feed reflects REALITY: if the job is still failing, \n  the error stays. If it succeeds, the error goes away.\n- The cron job entry in the Scheduler list should show an error \n  badge ONLY while there's an active unresolved error\n\n\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\nWHAT TO FIX NOW\n\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\n\n1. Fix the double-status bug (no more \"Completed\" + \"In Progress\" \n   showing simultaneously)\n2. Wire Investigate button to auto-create a task in the Tasks board\n3. Wire cron job success to auto-clear the corresponding error\n4. Wire cron job error badge to auto-clear when error is resolved\n5. Confirm Skip behaviour works as described above\n6. Test the full flow end-to-end\n\nReport what the current behaviour actually is, then fix it to \nmatch this spec.  [auto-dispatched 2026-06-01 11:53] [auto-dispatched 2026-06-02 11:59] [auto-dispatched 2026-06-02 12:29] [HEARTBEAT 2026-06-02 12:47: Task has been auto-dispatched 6+ times with zero progress. Setting stalledAt to prevent further re-dispatch. Needs human triage.] [auto-dispatched 2026-06-02 12:59] [auto-dispatched 2026-0